2. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) - The paper evaluates the performance of graph processing applications on different hardware architectures, including Intel Xeon E5 CPU, Nvidia Tesla P40 GPU, and Xeon Phi 7210 MIC processor, which falls under the category of hardware architecture. 
3. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - Graph processing is a common technique used in computational science and engineering, and the paper evaluates the performance of graph processing applications on different computing platforms, which is relevant to this sub-category. 
4. cs.DB (Databases) - Graph databases are becoming increasingly popular, and the paper evaluates the performance of graph processing applications on different computing platforms, which is relevant to this sub-category. 
5. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper evaluates the performance of graph processing applications on different computing platforms, which involves numerical analysis and optimization techniques, making it relevant to this sub-category.
